entries.entry: Started the class with several lightning exercises to focus on iterating. Moved onto API work throughout the day. Finished with work on Daily Journal.
Added radio buttons and worked with Brian to attach event listeners to them. The radio buttons should sort all of my entries by their mood key: value. Hope it works!
Trying to get my POST element to work and I need to mess around with fetch calls a little more if I'm going to get this to work.

Went over Browserify in the morning and covered set up as well as...breakdown. Well, I broke down my code after the fact. Spent the rest of the day working on exercise to build app for personal contacts. Actually finished relatively quickly. Feeling good about it!

Spent the morning watching Jenna live code. I'm spending the afternoon dialing in my daily journal. I'm having a hard time fetching all of my journal entries and I am taking time to fix all of those issues...

Learned ERD and data structures today, worked on related exercises and then had time after lunch to pick up slack on other projects. I spent a good part of the afternoon debugging my journal and adding a search function. I feel pretty good about the exercises we did this morning, although there is a jQuery advanced challenge that I still need to flex on.

Started the Nutshell project today. My group settled in classroom three and commandeered a white board with on which to fully flesh out our plan of attack. I think our group did a fantastic job laying out the data structure and we all gave each other a good laugh, which was good for keeping us focused. Warner and I played around with CSS ideas and we ended the day with several photos of iterations of the white boarding process to work with tomorrow.

Got an early start to the project this morning and made serious headway in it all throughout. We ended the day with all of the event listeners functioning and firing correctly. Spent the latter half of the afternoon with minor debugging which I think puts us in a good place for tomorrow, especially with it being a short, half-day. Hopefully we can take the leads we established today and apply them to quickly tackle (debug) our code and apply a little CSS to our Nutshell before the weekend. For Day 2 out of maybe 7(?), I think our group is up to something great!
